INSERT INTO AssessmentRecommendation VALUES(13,7,147,'Data Governance Organization','Data','Core',1.300000000000000044,4,2.700000000000000177,'P1','High Effort','["Establish a formal Data Governance Committee with NHS-compliant executive sponsorship, including Chief Medical Information Officer and representatives from all 14 integrated care systems, with defined meeting cadence and escalation procedures", "Convert existing draft governance roles and RACI documents into operational organizational structure by appointing certified data governance specialists and formalizing decision-making authority across clinical and IT stakeholders", "Implement enterprise data governance oversight processes for e-discovery, data sovereignty, and clinical data sourcing governance to meet GDPR and NHS digital standards requirements", "Deploy continuous improvement framework with defined accountability controls and compliance metrics for measuring governance maturity across all care systems", "Establish federated CDO role with oversight authority for entire data domain including security, access control, and AI-driven diagnostic data lineage"]','["Data Strategy", "Data Transformation"]','["Functional Data Governance Committee conducting monthly reviews with documented decisions within 90 days", "Certified governance specialists appointed and operational across all 14 integrated care systems within 120 days", "Measurable compliance metrics dashboard reporting GDPR and NHS digital standards adherence within 6 months"]','HPE Advisory & Professional Services can provide healthcare-specific data governance framework design and implementation, while HPE GreenLake can deliver the secure, compliant infrastructure platform required for federated clinical data management across integrated care systems.','HealthBridge Systems has strong foundational governance documentation but lacks the operational structure to enforce enterprise data governance across 14 care systems. The recommended path involves rapidly converting existing draft frameworks into functioning organizational capabilities with formal oversight committees and certified specialists, ensuring NHS compliance and enabling trusted AI-driven diagnostics through auditable data lineage.','2026-03-12T04:07:35.744120');
INSERT INTO AssessmentRecommendation VALUES(14,7,160,'Regulatory Compliance','Data','Core',2.0,4,2.0,'P1','High Effort','["Deploy enterprise data classification technology across all 14 integrated care systems to uniformly enforce the existing framework, with automated tagging of NHS patient data, GDPR-regulated personal data, and clinical research data", "Implement automated compliance monitoring and alerting system that tracks data handling violations across collection, processing, storage, and sharing lifecycle stages for NHS digital standards and GDPR requirements", "Deploy GRC platform integration to automatically monitor regulatory changes from NHS Digital, ICO, and MHRA, with automated assessment of impact on current data handling practices", "Establish automated audit trail generation for all clinical data flows between care systems, with real-time compliance scoring and exception reporting to designated accountability roles"]','[]','["100% of clinical and patient data automatically classified and tagged according to regulatory requirements within 90 days", "Automated detection and alerting of compliance violations across all 14 care systems with <24 hour response time", "Complete audit trail available for any clinical data element from source to AI diagnostic output within 5 minutes of request"]','HPE GreenLake for data governance and compliance automation, combined with HPE Ezmeral data fabric capabilities, directly address the automated monitoring and data classification requirements. HPE''s healthcare-specific compliance accelerators provide pre-configured NHS digital standards templates.','HealthBridge Systems has documented compliance frameworks but lacks the automation needed for reliable NHS digital standards adherence across 14 care systems. The critical gap is operational enforcement - without automated classification, monitoring, and auditing, manual compliance efforts cannot scale to support AI-driven diagnostics while maintaining regulatory trust. Implementing automated compliance technology will transform documented policies into enforceable, auditable data governance that enables safe clinical data sharing.','2026-03-12T04:07:35.744147');
